  "text": "Another novel finding in this study is that the attenuation of myofilament Ca 2+ sensitivity-observed in -MHC + RcTnT 1-43 fibers (Fig. 5 , A and C)-is ablated in -MHC + RcTnT 1-43 fibers (Fig. 5, B and D) . These observations clearly demonstrate that -and -MHC isoforms have a divergent impact on myofilament Ca 2+ sensitivity. Based on our recent studies, the attenuation of myofilament Ca 2+ sensitivity by RcTnT 1-43 may be explained by the RcTnT 1-43 -mediated increase in the rigidity of Tm [CITATION_1] . Such an impact on Tm would shift the OFF/ON equilibrium of the regulatory units (RUs; Tm-Tn) more toward the OFF state, thereby attenuating myofilament Ca 2+ sensitivity in -MHC + RcTnT 1-43 fibers. pCa 50 decreased significantly by 0.13 pCa units in -MHC + RcTnT 1-43 fibers (Fig. 5 C) but remained unaffected in -MHC + RcTnT 1-43 fibers (Fig. 5 D) , demonstrating that the augmenting effect of -MHC on thin filament cooperativity negated the attenuating effect of RcTnT 1-43 on myofilament Ca 2+ sensitivity. If this observation is true, we expect -MHC to further increase myofilament Ca 2+ sensi tivity in RcTnT 44-73 fibers. Indeed, that is exactly what we observe: for example, RcTnT 44-73 increases pCa 50 by 0.22 pCa units in the presence of -MHC and by 0.29 pCa units in the presence of -MHC. Inferences drawn from the above analysis lead us to conclude that on how the cardiac-specific N terminus of cTnT modulates cardiac thin filament activation. The magnitude of cardiac thin filament activation depends on how cooperative mechanisms are modulated by the actions of both cTnT and XBs. Thus, how the 1-44 and 45-74 regions of cTnT modulate thin filament activation and desensitize cardiac thin filaments to Ca 2+ [CITATION_2] will not only depend on how these two regions by themselves exert their effects on the thin filament but also on how such actions are further modulated by the MHC isoform-mediated effects on the thin filament.",
